PRIVACY POLICY
Effective Date: January 1, 2025
Monclarity, LLC (“Company,” “we,” “us,” or “our”) is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring transparency regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of your information. This Privacy Policy details how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information when you access our applications, websites, and services, or interact with us via support, social media, or email.
By using our services, you signify your acceptance of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to this policy, you must discontinue your use of our services.
1. Modifications to This Policy
We reserve the right to amend this Privacy Policy at any time. Any modifications will be reflected by updating the “Effective Date” at the top of this document. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to remain informed of how we protect your information.
2. Information We Collect
2.1 Categories of Information
We collect information directly from you, automatically through your interactions with our services, and from third parties. The categories of information we may collect include:
a. Usage Information:
Details regarding how you interact with our services, including features accessed, session durations, and return frequency.
b. Purchase Information:
Transaction data such as purchased items, payment details, and dates.
c. Log and Device Information:
Technical details about your device, including model, operating system, IP address, browser type, and navigation data.
d. Location Information:
Approximate geographic location derived from your IP address.
e. Information from Third Parties:
Data from linked third-party accounts (e.g., social media logins) with your authorization.
f. Inferences:
Profiles based on your preferences or characteristics derived from your activities.
2.2 Information from Cookies and Similar Technologies
We and our partners use cookies, device identifiers, and other technologies to collect non-personal and personal data for analytics, personalization, and advertising purposes. Most browsers allow you to manage or disable cookies through settings.
3. How We Use Your Information
We collect information directly from you, automatically through your interactions with our services, and from third parties. The categories of information we may collect include:
Provide and improve our services.
Process transactions and manage your account.
Analyze trends, monitor performance, and enhance user experience.
Detect and prevent fraud or other unauthorized activities.
Comply with legal and regulatory obligations.
Personalize your experience and deliver targeted advertising.
4. Sharing Your Information
4.1 Authorized Sharing
We may share your information in the following circumstances:
Service Providers:
To facilitate operations such as payment processing, analytics, and customer support.
Legal Compliance:
To comply with laws, regulations, or legal processes.
Corporate Transactions:
During mergers, acquisitions, or asset transfers.
Advertising Partners:
To deliver personalized advertising based on your preferences and activity.
Aggregated Data:
For research and operational purposes without personally identifying you.
5. Your Choices and Rights
5.1 Managing Communication Preferences
You may unsubscribe from promotional emails by following the instructions included in each email. To unsubscribe from third-party communications, contact the respective third parties.
5.2 Controlling Targeted Advertising
You can limit interest-based advertising by adjusting your device settings (e.g., “Limit Ad Tracking” on iOS or “Opt-out of Interest-Based Ads” on Android).
5.3 Accessing, Updating, or Deleting Data
To request access to or deletion of your personal information, submit a request through our app settings or email us at privacy@monclarity.com. Deletion requests may take up to 30 days to process and may not include data already shared with third parties under this policy.
6. Data Security
We implement industry-standard measures, including encryption, firewalls, and access restrictions, to safeguard your information. However, no system is completely secure. You use our services at your own risk.
If you identify a potential security vulnerability, report it to privacy@monclarity.com.
7. Additional Information for California Residents
7.1 California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
This section applies solely to California residents and describes their rights under the CCPA:
Access and Portability:
Request information about data collected, used, and shared.
Deletion:
Request deletion of personal information, subject to legal exceptions.
Opt-Out:
Direct businesses to stop selling personal information.
To exercise these rights, submit a verifiable consumer request through our “Contact Us” form or email us.
7.2 Categories of Personal Information Collected
We collect the following categories:
Personal identifiers (e.g., name, email, IP address).
Commercial data (e.g., purchase history).
Device and network activity (e.g., browsing behavior).
Inferences based on user activity.
8. Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your rights, contact us via:
Website Form:
Use the “Contact Us” section on our website.
Email:
privacy@monclarity.com.
This Privacy Policy constitutes the entire agreement governing your use of Monclarity’s services and supersedes prior agreements on this subject.
